{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592945","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592945"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:20:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:20:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15290"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15290","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15290"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7981"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69019"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7981","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7981"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15290"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54476"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19417"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19418"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69019","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69019"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA liver biopsy specimen shows hepatocytes containing eosinophilic intracytoplasmic inclusions composed of aggregated intermediate filaments.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this histological feature?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Apoptotic bodies","Ground glass hepatocytes","Mallory bodies","Nuclear vacuolation","Viral inclusions"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe specimen shows \u003Cstrong\u003EMallory bodies\u003C/strong\u003E, which are eosinophilic intracytoplasmic inclusions composed of aggregated intermediate filaments. They are commonly found in alcoholic liver disease but can also occur in other conditions like non-alcoholic steatohepatitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApoptotic bodies\u003C/strong\u003E are condensed cellular fragments resulting from programmed cell death\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGround glass hepatocytes\u003C/strong\u003E show a frosted glass appearance due to accumulated viral proteins in hepatitis B infection\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENuclear vacuolation\u003C/strong\u003E refers to clear spaces within nuclei and is non-specific\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EViral inclusions\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic nuclear or cytoplasmic changes seen with cytomegalovirus and other viral infections\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMallory bodies are an important histological marker of hepatocyte injury, particularly in alcoholic liver disease where they occur alongside hepatocyte ballooning and fatty change.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Mallory bodies (also called Mallory-Denk bodies) are eosinophilic intracytoplasmic inclusions composed of aggregated intermediate filaments in damaged hepatocytes.","Mallory bodies are characteristic of alcoholic liver disease but can also be found in non-alcoholic steatohepatitis and other liver conditions.","Histological features of alcoholic liver disease include hepatocyte ballooning, Mallory bodies, and steatosis."],"references":["Mallory body high mag. by Nephron is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license. https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mallory_body_high_mag.jpg","Torbenson M, Washington K. Pathology of liver disease: advances in the last 50 years. Hum Pathol. 2020 Jan;95:78-98. doi: 10.1016/j.humpath.2019.08.023. Epub 2019 Sep 4. PMID: 31493428","Chan WK, Chuah KH, Rajaram RB, Lim LL, Ratnasingam J, Vethakkan SR. Metabolic Dysfunction-Associated Steatotic Liver Disease (MASLD): A State-of-the-Art Review. J Obes Metab Syndr. 2023 Sep 30;32(3):197-213. doi: 10.7570/jomes23052. Epub 2023 Sep 13. PMID: 37700494; PMCID: PMC10583766","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: 10.1016/j.cld.2019.09.004. Epub 2019 Oct 31. PMID: 31753251; PMCID: PMC6986808"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54476"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15290"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21151"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21151","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21151"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5fGzjlOCiWHApiMpjIMZP5qZaKXwv9.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5fGzjlOCiWHApiMpjIMZP5qZaKXwv9.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":1200}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54476","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54476"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-10T20:32:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-10T20:34:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7981"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69019"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relation